@@TJvExCustomMaskEdit
Summary
  Base class for extended masked edit controls.
Description
  TJvExCustomMaskEdit is a base class for classes in the JVCL library that descend from TCustomMaskEdit.

  Do not create instances of TJvExCustomMaskEdit. Use a descendant of TJvExCustomMaskEdit or create your
  own descendant class.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvExCustomMaskEdit.AboutJVCL
<INCLUDE JVCL.Main.AboutJVCL.dtx>
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvExCustomMaskEdit.BeepOnError
Summary
  Specifies whether the edit control beeps when the user tries to enter text that does not match the mask.
Description
  If BeepOnError is true (the default), the application beeps when a validation error occurs.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvExCustomMaskEdit.ClipboardCommands
Summary
  Specifies the clipboard commands that are enabled for the control.
Description
  Use ClipboardCommands to specify which clipboard commands are allowed for the edit control.

  * ClipboardCommands can't be set to [].
  * If ClipboardCommands is set to [caCopy] then property ReadOnly is set to True.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvExCustomMaskEdit.OnMouseEnter
Summary
  Occurs when the mouse pointer moves over the control.
Description
  Write an OnMouseEnter event handler to take specific action when the user moves the mouse over the
  control.
See Also
  OnMouseLeave
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvExCustomMaskEdit.OnMouseLeave
Summary
  Occurs when the mouse pointer moves off the control.
Description
  Write an OnMouseLeave event handler to take specific action when the user moves the mouse off the
  control. For example, you can use this event to undo changes that were made in an OnMouseEnter
  event handler.
See Also
  OnMouseEnter
